{
  "id": "RAW_e309be",
  "title": "Vercel v0:连接设计与代码，加速开发流程",
  "url": "https://vercel.com/blog/bridging-the-gap-between-design-and-code-with-v0",
  "date": "2025-02-12 13:00:00",
  "author": "Peri Langlois",
  "siteName": "Vercel News",
  "content": "\n \n \n  <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack article_content__xNUGz\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:24px\" data-customer-story=\"false\">\n   <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack article_dateAndTimeToRead__6RnTk\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:row;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:space-between;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n    <div class=\"flex items-center gap-x-2 sm:gap-x-6\">\n     <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:row;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:6px\">\n      <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:0.875rem;--text-line-height:1.25rem;--text-letter-spacing:0px;--text-weight:400\"><br></p></div></div></div>\n   <div class=\"article_leadIn__vSmkA\">\n    <p>How Speakeasy uses v0 to ship faster with features like Figma import and custom Tailwind config.</p>\n   </div>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\"><a href=\"http://speakeasy.com/?utm_source=vercel\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link_link__hbWKh link_highlight__kJZF9\">Speakeasy</a> specializes in building developer-focused SDKs—<!-- -->to help developers build their products.<!-- --> <!-- -->They adopted v0 to bridge the workflow from design to code, using it to accelerate rapid prototyping and reduce implementation time.</p>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Speakeasy's product is highly technical, and their team embraces a \"design as code\" philosophy. Without <a href=\"https://v0.dev/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link_link__hbWKh link_highlight__kJZF9\">v0</a>, this approach wasn’t straightforward. While Figma is used for initial design explorations, static pixel designs weren't enough to convey new ideas or get buy-in. Design at Speakeasy focuses on movement, behavior, and interaction—how a product feels, not just how it looks. Given the need for quick iteration, meticulously designing every feature in Figma wasn’t practical.</p>\n   <figure class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_media__17gkA\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:16px\">\n    <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_outside__8KjIr\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n     <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_inside__Mq7tv\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n      <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"544\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image_intrinsic__ulrJk blog-mode-dependent-media_addPadding__lfHNN\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/4p2km18eEgKFX4Qb08dhYz/a5d93a10039a562d99c30da81679f0cb/Screenshot_2025-02-03_at_11.10.13_AM.png, https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/4p2km18eEgKFX4Qb08dhYz/a5d93a10039a562d99c30da81679f0cb/Screenshot_2025-02-03_at_11.10.13_AM.png\" src=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/4p2km18eEgKFX4Qb08dhYz/a5d93a10039a562d99c30da81679f0cb/Screenshot_2025-02-03_at_11.10.13_AM.png\">\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </figure>\n   <h2 class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_subheading__5II6M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"text_subheadingAnchor__eW51P\" href=\"#using-v0-to-iterate-on-experiences-faster\" id=\"using-v0-to-iterate-on-experiences-faster\">Using v0 to iterate on experiences faster \n     <svg class=\"text_hash__wLjCi\" data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg></a></h2>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">v0 helps the whole Speakeasy team quickly explore ideas, even if they’re not designers or engineers.</p>\n   <figure class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_media__17gkA\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:16px\">\n    <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_outside__8KjIr\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n     <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_inside__Mq7tv\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n      <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"563\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image_intrinsic__ulrJk blog-mode-dependent-media_addPadding__lfHNN\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2wWOiJ2Ftndf6ohGW0luPK/3fb17897a5f28114d247528b12573e70/CleanShot_2025-02-12_at_10.57.57_2x.png, https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2wWOiJ2Ftndf6ohGW0luPK/3fb17897a5f28114d247528b12573e70/CleanShot_2025-02-12_at_10.57.57_2x.png\" src=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2wWOiJ2Ftndf6ohGW0luPK/3fb17897a5f28114d247528b12573e70/CleanShot_2025-02-12_at_10.57.57_2x.png\">\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </figure>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">They use v0 as a dynamic design descriptor, a way to share interactive prototypes and demonstrate feature behavior. Some designs start in <a href=\"https://vercel.com/blog/working-with-figma-and-custom-design-systems-in-v0-6cZjvh5CBjx0d3ZF967jGj\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link_link__hbWKh link_highlight__kJZF9\">Figma and are imported into v0</a>, but many concepts are designed directly in v0. This allows, designers and engineers collaborate in real time, refining ideas without the friction of design-to-code translation.</p>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">For instance, the<b> initial concept for the Terminal Preview in the Speakeasy dashboard was created in a single day using v0.</b> This rapid prototyping allowed the team to focus on refining interactivity and user experience rather than translating static designs into code.</p>\n   <figure class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_media__17gkA blog-video-asset_videoWrapper__RSAt5\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:16px\">\n    <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_outside__8KjIr blog-video-asset_videoBorder__Kuumi\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"aspect-ratio:3020/920;--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n     <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_inside__Mq7tv\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n      <figure class=\"video_figure__rlLg4 video_oversize__n2jkl\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--video-margin:0px;--video-width:min(3020px, 950px)\">\n       <div class=\"video_main__8vED4\" style=\"width:100%;\"></div>\n      </figure>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <figcaption class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK blog-media_caption__fNFzJ\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:0.875rem;--text-line-height:1.25rem;--text-letter-spacing:initial;--text-weight:400;--text-align:center\">\n     The team used v0 to design the look and the feel of their Terminal Preview feature, including the polished interactions.\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <blockquote class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack quote_quoteContainer__oBLby\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--sm-stack-gap:24px;--md-stack-gap:24px;--lg-stack-gap:32px;--xl-stack-gap:32px\">\n    <div class=\"quote_quote__nPfu2\">\n     <span class=\"geist-sr-only\">The reason I jumped to v0, was a bias towards code. It meant less time having to redo ideas in Figma. When it comes to getting ready to ship, I was already in the right medium. I saved whatever time it would have taken me to translate Figma to code.\"</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack quote_author__RduX2\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--sm-stack-direction:column;--md-stack-direction:row;--sm-stack-align:flex-end;--md-stack-align:center;--stack-justify:flex-end;--stack-padding:0px;--sm-stack-gap:8px;--md-stack-gap:12px;--lg-stack-gap:12px;--xl-stack-gap:12px\">\n     <span aria-label=\"\" class=\"avatar_avatar__3ccqO\" data-geist-avatar=\"\" data-mask=\"true\" data-resolved=\"false\" data-version=\"v1\" role=\"img\" style=\"--size:24px\"><img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" loading=\"eager\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" decoding=\"sync\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image_intrinsic__ulrJk\" style=\"color:transparent\" src=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2hTHjI1KkeNFrpDCanLqUR/1ba8ce66666207d2d5dc9d320f36cd43/image.png\"></span>\n     <div>\n      <span class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK quote_author-text__NkaxZ\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--xs-text-size:0.875rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.25rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:0px;--sm-text-size:0.875rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.25rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:0px;--smd-text-size:0.875rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.25rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:0px;--md-text-size:0.875rem;--md-text-line-height:1.25rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:0px;--lg-text-size:1rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:0px\"><strong>Faraz Khan<!-- -->, </strong> Design Engineer </span>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </blockquote>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">A key element of their workflow is a custom Tailwind configuration, which v0 users use to build and style components according to their design system. <!-- -->For example, the font weights and colors used in their Terminal Preview feature were all defined and used within v0.</p>\n   <figure class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_media__17gkA\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:center;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:16px\">\n    <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_outside__8KjIr\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n     <div class=\"stack_stack__iZkUS stack blog-media_inside__Mq7tv\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:stretch;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n      <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"Example of defining custom style preferences in the tailwind.config.js file in v0. \" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"476\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image_intrinsic__ulrJk blog-mode-dependent-media_addPadding__lfHNN image_lightMode__SmqSs\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2E6WFdOUTkK9fGdfazpEqS/67f01a0f5e4e8f82e05b48dfcfda526b/Screenshot_2025-01-22_at_10.26.27_AM.png, https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2E6WFdOUTkK9fGdfazpEqS/67f01a0f5e4e8f82e05b48dfcfda526b/Screenshot_2025-01-22_at_10.26.27_AM.png\" src=\"https://assets.vercel.com/image/upload/contentful/image/e5382hct74si/2E6WFdOUTkK9fGdfazpEqS/67f01a0f5e4e8f82e05b48dfcfda526b/Screenshot_2025-01-22_at_10.26.27_AM.png\">\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <figcaption class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK blog-media_caption__fNFzJ\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:0.875rem;--text-line-height:1.25rem;--text-letter-spacing:initial;--text-weight:400;--text-align:center\">\n     Example of defining custom style preferences in the tailwind.config.js file in v0.\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Everyone from designers to backend developers at Speakeasy use v0. The team often shares Loom recordings of their v0 prototypes to communicate design ideas effectively. In fact, the phrase “Share a v0” has replaced lengthy Slack discussions and meetings.</p>\n   <p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">By prototyping directly in a code-native environment, Speakeasy accelerates iteration, improves product quality, and keeps design and engineering in sync. For them, v0 isn't just a tool—it’s how they build better developer experiences.</p><p class=\"text_wrapper__i87JK text_paragraph__8ua7M\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\"></p>\n  </div>\n \n",
